The paper focuses on few-shot learning using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves a novel meta-learning approach and a dropout technique, which are also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of shared weight generation, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE).
